### Test Analytics Insights Endpoint
### GET /gov/analytics/insights
### Requirements: 7.1, 7.2, 7.3, 7.4

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api/v1
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Test insights endpoint without cached data (should return placeholder)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/insights
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected Response:
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "data": {
#     "insights": ["Insight AI sedang dihasilkan. Silakan cek kembali dalam beberapa saat."],
#     "generatedAt": null
#   }
# }

### 2. Test insights endpoint with cached data
### First, manually set cache data in Redis:
### redis-cli
### SET "analytics:insights:YOUR_AGENCY_ID" '{"insights":["Laporan jalan rusak meningkat 25% minggu ini","Kategori lampu jalan memiliki waktu penyelesaian tercepat"],"generatedAt":"2024-01-15T10:30:00.000Z"}'

GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/insights
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected Response:
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "data": {
#     "insights": [
#       "Laporan jalan rusak meningkat 25% minggu ini",
#       "Kategori lampu jalan memiliki waktu penyelesaian tercepat"
#     ],
#     "generatedAt": "2024-01-15T10:30:00.000Z"
#   }
# }

### 3. Test as officer (should use officer's agency)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/insights
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Test as super admin (should use 'all' key)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/insights
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Test without authentication (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/insights

### Expected Response:
# {
#   "success": false,
#   "error": {
#     "code": "UNAUTHORIZED",
#     "message": "Token tidak valid atau telah kedaluwarsa"
#   }
# }
